condition.narrative: Should contribute directly to results for children as outlined in the UNDAF, national results and/or UNICEF Strategic Plan and within the scope defined in the CPD, CPAP, OMP or other agreed upon programme documents

title.narrative: By 2020, children, especially the most vulnerable, have access to a child - friendly justice system which adequately responds to children’s violation of rights and ensures fair, timely and effective solutions

description.narrative: With UNICEF support, further progress was made in implementation of the Juvenile Justice Code, capacity building and specialization of justice professionals and creation of a comprehensive data collection system. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:17/12/2019

title.narrative: Existence of specialized justice for children systems, such as capacity building and standards-setting within criminal and civil justice systems

target.value: 2019:Specialization for professionals institutionalized, regulations in place

actual.value: 2020:Ordinance for specialization of professionals from the criminal justice system adopted, training programmes institutionalized. Child Rights Code provides for extension of justice for children approach to civil justice system

title.narrative: National rule of law, access to justice, justice sector reform policies, strategies and plans (or equivalent) incorporate issues pertaining to children

baseline.value: Procedures and services exist in the criminal justice system (JJ code) only and would need to be strengthened. Procedures and services to be developed for the civil and administrative justice system

target.value: 2019:Data collection and analysis system on children victims and witness of crimes and children in conflict with the law is operational

actual.value: 2019:Child friendly environment, comprehensive data collection and analysis system, quality assurance and supervision systems, central and regional multidisciplinary mechanisms established based on concepts and related instruments developed by UNICEF.
